BLUK


PLANET:       Bluk
TYPE:         Terrestrial planet, Trade and tourist center
CLIMATE:      Mild, suitable for many races
MOONS:        Unknown
TERRAIN:      Red sands radiating light, blue skies, urban agglomerations
LOCATION:     Bluk star system, Sector 8 of the Milky Way Galaxy
NATIVE RACES: Ushan (natives), The Speaking Birds (intelligent birds), numerous visitors from across the galaxy
AFFILIATION:  Independent world, active participant in intergalactic trade
LOCATIONS:    Palaputra City, Palaputra Spaceport, Philatelic Market, Main The Speaking Bird Nursery

DESCRIPTION:

This planet is a busy crossroads of space routes, one of the key trade and tourist planets Galaxies. Unlike many worlds, it is not closed off, but open to countless visitors from all corners of space. The planet is known for its vibrant landscape, described by poets as a combination of "red sky and blue sand."

The main center of civilization on Bluk is the city of Palaputra, almost entirely built up with warehouses and hotels designed to accommodate a wide variety of life forms. The Palaputra spaceport is one of the largest in the sector, capable of handling numerous passenger and charter flights daily.

The planet's indigenous inhabitants are the Ushan, intelligent humanoids named for their large, mobile ears. For them, ears are not just a hearing organ, but a vital communication tool. In addition to normal speech, Ushan possess a secret language based on complex ear movements. In moments of fear, they press their ears back, and when embarrassed, they cover their faces with them. When arguing, Ushan bats can create gusts of wind capable of blowing heavy objects off tables.

Bluk is also home to unique intelligent birds called The Speaking Birds. These creatures possess a phenomenal memory (remembering everything they see and hear) and are capable of interstellar travel at superluminal speeds.

The planet is home to the main The Speaking Bird breeding ground in all of inhabited space.

KEY LOCATIONS:

- Palaputra City: The capital and only major city on the planet, built around a spaceport. The architecture is oriented toward serving tourists and traders: countless hotels, warehouses, and rest areas for creatures from various planets.
- Palaputra Spaceport: A massive transportation hub, handling scheduled and charter flights from across the galaxy. One of the busiest spaceports in the sector.
- Philatelic Market: The largest stamp market in the galaxy, second only to the market in the Andromeda Nebula. Billions of collectors gather here every week. The area is divided into 14,300 tables, where philatelists from different planets exchange stamps. Here you can find the rarest specimens, including the legendary stamps from the planet Sheshineru (the uncanceled ones change their image on even numbers, and the canceled ones are completely blank) and the engineering marvel of albums from the planet Fix, which automatically place stamps in the correct place. - Main Talking Bird Nursery: The center for the breeding and preservation of unique talking birds. The only place in the galaxy where you can be guaranteed to purchase or order this rare bird.
